<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06361190 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06361190 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  CHEMICAL; PLANT; PARIS  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A unit of W.R. Grace andamp; Co. hopes to capitalize on a unified European market bybuilding a $30 million manufacturing plant near Paris.;   Grace SpecialtyChemicals, one of the businesses that survived Grace's recently announceddivestiture plan, will build the plant in Epernon, France, about 40 milessouthwest of Paris. The plant will be so sophisticated that it will employonly 50 people, a spokesman for the Boca Raton-based company said last week.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  GRACE PLANS HUGE PLANT NEAR PARIS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Grace will use the plant to make plastic sealing compounds found on bottlesand other containers. That work is now done in two plants in Great Britain andone in Italy.;   The spokesman said the company &quot;is not prepared&quot; to say whatwill become of those older plants. He said the new plant will offer 20 percentmore production capacity.;   &quot;By centralizing production in the containerbusiness, Grace's Epernon container expansion will place Grace in a betterposition to compete in the European market in the 1990s,&quot; said Donald H.Kohnken, president of Grace Specialty Chemicals.;   Grace recently unveiled a$1.5 billion restructuring program that involved the sell-off of severalbusinesses not related to specialty chemicals or medical services. The companysaid the proceeds would be used to pay down debt and invest in research anddevelopment.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Knight-Ridder News Service  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Boca Raton, Fla.  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911226  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4E  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  213  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, December 26, 1991